      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Wet avalanches can in isolated cases be released by a single winter sport participant. This applies especially below approximately 2600 m. <br/> <br/> As a consequence of new snow and a moderate wind, clearly visible wind slabs will form in particular in high Alpine regions. These are small and can only be released in isolated cases. <br/> <br/> Weak layers in the old snowpack can be released in isolated cases and mostly by large additional loads in particular on very steep shady slopes, in particular above approximately 2500 m.",
        "highlights": "Wet snow requires caution."
      },
